  <section class="introduction">
    <h2>About Me</h2>
    <%= image_tag 'milesImages/img_4.png', alt: 'Miles in Seattle', class: 'feature-image small-image' %>
    <p> Greetings, I am Miles Cook Menster, a dedicated and driven 21-year-old senior at the University of Iowa,
      pursuing a degree in Electrical Engineering with a focus on computer systems.
      Hailing from the small town of Bloomfield, Iowa, I am poised to graduate in May 2024, equipped with a passion
      for leveraging electrical and computer engineering to make a positive impact on society. </p>
  </section>

  <!--  Section template-->
  <section class="SECTION">
    <h2>Academic Pursuits</h2>
    <%= image_tag 'milesImages/img_3.png', alt: '"The Moth" project for embedded systems', class: 'feature-image small-image' %>
    <p> My academic journey has been centered around the convergence of electrical engineering and computer science.
      I am enthusiastic about delving into the intricacies of these fields, driven by a desire to contribute meaningfully to
      technological advancements. As a graduating senior, I aspire to channel my expertise towards enhancing sustainability
      and minimizing our environmental footprint. In the accompanied image, you can see my final project for embedded systems. It
      was a mobile system called "The Moth" which used photo resistors to seek out the brightest point in a room. It would then utilize an embedded C
      program to move towards the highest concentration of light. It also utilized an ultrasonic sensor and dual servo motors to move. One of the coolest
      projects I have had to opportunity to work on -- especially fulfilling to see the final result.</p>
  </section>

  <!--  Section template-->
  <section class="SECTION">
    <h2>Values and Skills</h2>
    <%= image_tag 'milesImages/img_1.png', alt: 'Miles at his 7th Birthday', class: 'feature-image small-image' %>
    <p> I am a firm believer in the value of hard work and collaboration. My dedication to personal and professional
      growth is complemented by a strong work ethic, effective communication skills, and a collaborative mindset.
      I am adept at navigating the intersection of programming and electronics, and I approach challenges with an
      open mind, always eager to learn and adapt. Ever since I was a kid I had a passion for working towards my goals (and apple fritters of course). </p>
  </section>

  <!--  Section template-->
  <section class="SECTION">
    <h2>Work Experience</h2>
    <%= image_tag 'milesImages/img_5.png', alt: 'Miles in front of Arconic factory', class: 'feature-image small-image' %>
    <p> As an Electrical Engineering Intern at Arconic, I collaborated with a diverse team to troubleshoot production lines
      and contribute to projects, gaining hands-on experience in advanced skills like 5000-level PLC programming and HMI configuration.
      This internship provided a deep understanding of the industry and emphasized effective teamwork. My Summer Member role at
      Green Iowa AmeriCorps further honed my collaborative skills in community-focused initiatives. Additionally, working as a
      summer custodian at the University of Iowa enhanced my adaptability and interpersonal skills within a diverse work environment.
      These experiences collectively strengthened my technical prowess while emphasizing the significance of teamwork, community engagement,
      and adaptability in professional settings. </p>
  </section>

  <!--  Section template-->
